### English Title:
Shooting at Florida State University Leaves Two Dead and Several Injured

### English Text Summary:
The article reports on a shooting incident at Florida State University, where two individuals were killed and five others injured. The victims were not students at the university. The shooter was also injured and has been arrested. A student described the situation as "very scary." President Donald Trump condemned the shooting as "shameful" but indicated he is unlikely to pursue changes to gun laws, emphasizing his support for the Second Amendment. He mentioned that the issue of gun violence is complex and not solely attributable to firearms but to individuals. The article also notes Trump's previous openness to background checks for gun buyers, which he later retracted.

